text: Donald Miranda (born 19 October 1972) is a retired Italian diver. He was born in Turin. At the 2000 Olympic Games he finished 16th in the 3 metre springboard event and eighth together with Nicola Marconi in the synchronized 3 metre springboard event. ==References== Category:1972 births Category:Living people Category:Italian male divers Category:Divers at the 2000 Summer Olympics Category:Olympic divers of Italy Category:Divers of Centro Sportivo Carabinieri
